    <string name="dialog_text_import">Please locate the ZIP file you would like to import. The imported data will overwrite any existing data.</string>
    <string name="dialog_notes_import"><b>If you have modified the CSV files:</b>\n\n<ul>
        <li>The CSV files must be put into a zip file in order to import.\n\n</li>
        <li>Specific values are expected in the header row. If you\'ve changed any of the header row values, you must change them back. You can create a new export to find the appropriate values.</li></ul>
    </string>
    <string name="dialog_text_export">This will create a ZIP file containing a CSV-formatted backup of your data.</string>
    <string name="dialog_notes_export"><ul>
        <li>Choose a secure location to save the ZIP file and any extracted files, as anyone with access to them will be able to open them.\n\n</li>
        <li>Creating a manual backup is purely optional, because Android already periodically backs up your app data, if you have it enabled in <b>Settings > System > Backup</b>. Any time you reinstall the app, your data will be automatically restored from the last available backup.</li></ul>
    </string>

